(105, 'Bhavnagar', '1', 'harshit', 'Bhavnagar.jpg', '5', 'In the Saurashtra Region of Gujarat State, there is a port city called Bhavnagar. It is situated approximately 198 kilometers away from Gandhinagar, the state capital. The town appeal draws a sizable number of visitors each year. Among the most well-liked sights in the city are the Takhteshwar Temple, Gaurishankar Lake, Victoria Park, Nilambag Palace, Shri Adishwar Temple, and numerous other locations. Blackbuck National Park is home to numerous bird species, blue bulls (nilgai), and blackbuck. The fact that so many migratory species pass through this area each winter is beneficial to birdwatchers. Do not forget to indulge in the well-known Gujarati dish \"Gathiya\" while you are in Bhavnagar.\r\n', '', '', '1', '4', '2330', 'bhavnagar.jpg,Bhavnagar (3).jpg,Bhavnagar (2).jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/rETmwfNakyfefCLJ7'),
(106, 'Vadodara', '`1', 'harshit', 'Vadodara (2).jpg', '5', 'The third-largest city in Gujarat is the multicultural city of Vadodara, which is situated on the banks of the Vishwamitri River. Because of the Jain, Islamic, and Hindu dynasties that have ruled over it, it is also known as the cultural capital. The captivating city welcomes a diverse range of tourists with its numerous captivating architectural landmarks, historic monuments, historic palaces, lovely parks, museums, and art galleries.\r\n', '', '', '1', '1', '1', 'vadodra (1).jpg,Vadodara (3).jpg,Vadodara.jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/rETmwfNakyfefCLJ7'),
(107, ' MountAbu', '1', 'harshit', 'Mount Abu.jpg', '6', 'Travel to Mount Abu is growing in popularity these days. The greatest place to get customized vacation packages for Mount Abu is Skyglobals. ', '', '', '1', '1', '2', ',MountAbu (2).jpg,MountAbu.jpg', ''),
(108, 'Ranakpur ', '1', 'harshit', 'Ranakpur .jpg', '6', 'In the Pali district of Rajasthan in western India, the village of Ranakpur is situated in Desuri tehsil close to Sadri town.\r\n', '', '', '2', '5', '3000', ',Ranakpur (3).jpg,Ranakpur (2).jpg,Ranakpur.jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/QUE6ZaPZGRCCbKt68'),
(110, 'Prayagraj', '1', 'harshit', 'Prayagraj.jpg', '9', 'Prayagraj, formerly known as Allahabad or Ilahabad, is a metropolis in the Indian state of Uttar Pradesh. It is the administrative headquarters of the Prayagraj district, the most populous district in the state and 13th most populous district in India and the Prayagraj division.', '', '', '2', '1', '10', 'Prayagraj (4).jpg,Prayagraj (3).jpg,Prayagraj (2).jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/QUE6ZaPZGRCCbKt68'),
(111, 'Neil Island', '1', 'harshit', 'neil island.jpg', '10', 'Neil Island is one of Indiaâ€™s Andaman Islands, in the Bay of Bengal. Bharatpur Beach has coral reefs teeming with tropical fish.\r\n', '', '', '1', '2', '2', 'Havelock .jpg,neil island.jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/rETmwfNakyfefCLJ7'),
(112, 'Leh', '1', 'harshit', 'leh (1).jpg', '11', 'Leh is a city in the disputed area of Kashmir, located in Ladakh. It is Ladakh\'s largest city and joint capital.\r\n', '', '', '1', '1', '3000', 'leh (1).jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/rETmwfNakyfefCLJ7'),
(113, ' Kanchipuram ', '1', 'harshit', 'kanchipuram.jpg', '23', 'Kanchipuram, also known as Kanchi, is an ancient city in southern Indiaâ€™s Tamil Nadu state', '', '', '1', '1', '2', 'kanchipuram.jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/rETmwfNakyfefCLJ7'),
(114, ' Pondicherry ', '1', 'harshit', 'Pondicherry .jpg', '23', 'Pondicherry (or Puducherry), a French colonial settlement in India until 1954, is now a Union Territory town bounded by the southeastern Tamil Nadu state.', '', '', '1', '1', '10', 'Pondicherry .jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/rETmwfNakyfefCLJ7'),
(115, 'Tiruvannamalai ', '1', 'harshit', 'Tiruvannamalai.jpg', '23', 'Tiruvannamalai is a city, a spiritual, cultural, economic hub and also the administrative headquarters of Tiruvannamalai District in the Indian state of Tamil Nadu. ', '', '', '2', '1', '10', 'Tiruvannamalai.jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/QUE6ZaPZGRCCbKt68'),
(116, 'Madurai ', '1', 'harshit', 'Madurai .jpg', '23', 'Madurai is an energetic, ancient city on the Vaigai River in the South Indian state of Tamil Nadu.', '', '', '2', '4', '10', 'Madurai .jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/QUE6ZaPZGRCCbKt68'),
(117, 'Chennai', '1', 'harshit', 'Chennai.jpg', '23', 'Chennai, on the Bay of Bengal in eastern India, is the capital of the state of Tamil Nadu. ', '', '', '1', '5', '10', 'Chennai.jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/QUE6ZaPZGRCCbKt68'),
(118, 'Ooty', '1', 'harshit', 'ooty.jpg', '23', 'Ooty (short for Udhagamandalam) is a resort town in the Western Ghats mountains, in southern India\'s Tamil Nadu state.', '', '', '5', '5', '2', 'ooty.jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/rETmwfNakyfefCLJ7'),
(119, 'Rameswaram ', '1', 'harshit', 'Rameswaram .jpg', '23', 'Char Dham v t e Jagannath Puri Rameswaram Dwarka Badrinath Ramanathaswamy Temple is a Hindu temple dedicated to the Hindu god Shiva located on Rameswaram island in the state of Tamil Nadu, India. It is also one of the twelve Jyotirlinga temples.', '', '', '1', '1', '3000', 'Rameswaram .jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/QUE6ZaPZGRCCbKt68'),
(120, 'yelagiri', '1', 'harshit', 'yelagiri (1).jpg', '23', 'Yelagiri is a hill station in the southeast Indian state of Tamil Nadu. Built in 1964, the hilltop Velavan Temple is a colorful Murugan temple with views of the valley below. ', '', '', '1', '1', '10', 'yelagiri (1).jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/rETmwfNakyfefCLJ7'),
(121, 'Kanyakumari ', '1', 'harshit', 'Kanyakumari .jpg', '23', 'Kanyakumari is a coastal town in the state of Tamil Nadu on India\'s southern tip. ', '', '', '1', '1', '2', 'Kanyakumari .jpg', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/rETmwfNakyfefCLJ7'),
(122, 'Darjeeling', '1', 'Shiv', 'darjeeling1 (2).jpg', '146', 'Nestled in the Indian state of West Bengal, Darjeeling is well-known for its diverse culture, tea estates, and stunning scenery. Situated above the Himalayan foothills, it provides sweeping vistas of snow-capped peaks and verdant surroundings. Famously, the area produces the world-famous Darjeeling tea, which is prized for its distinct flavour and scent. In addition to its tea gardens, Darjeeling is known for its bustling marketplaces, colonial buildings, and Buddhist monasteries, all of which are remnants of the region\'s diverse past. It is a popular destination for both nature lovers and adventure seekers, as they may hike via its lovely trails or discover its stunning grandeur via the UNESCO World Heritage Site, the Darjeeling Himalayan Railway.', '', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Darjeeling1 (4).jpg,Darjeeling2 (2).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d56862.46622278856!2d88.26467505000001!3d27.0331949!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39e42e654cf501bb%3A0x4175555979d4702a!2sDarjeeling%2C%20West%20Bengal!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v17181691'),
(123, 'Rohtang', '1', 'Shiv', 'Rohtang.jpg', '1', 'The state of Himachal Pradesh in India is home to Rohtang Pass, which serves as a gateway to the breathtaking Himalayas. Situated at a height beyond 3,900 metres, it presents breathtaking views of snow-covered peaks, glaciers, and alpine meadows. Rohtang Pass, a vital route connecting the Kullu Valley to the Lahaul and Spiti Valleys, is well-known for its difficult terrain and erratic weather, drawing tourists and thrill-seekers from all over the world. It\'s a haven for nature lovers and adrenaline addicts alike, with a wide range of activities available to visitors, including trekking and sightseeing in the warmer months and skiing and snowboarding in the winter.', '', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Rohtang (3).jpg,Rohtang (2).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d6739.538591077475!2d77.24168659024863!3d32.37173390686551!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39047ef0b27a15ad%3A0xbfdd7e65efefc66b!2sRohtang%20La!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1718170597205!5m2!'),
(124, 'Gangtok', '1', 'Shiv', 'Gangtok (2).jpg', '21', 'The capital of the Indian state of Sikkim, Gangtok, offers a mesmerising fusion of contemporary conveniences, natural beauty, and cultural diversity. It is tucked away in the Eastern Himalayas and offers expansive views of verdant valleys, snow-capped peaks, and gushing waterfalls. Gangtok, which is well-known for its busy markets, clean streets, and monasteries, provides a tranquil haven amidst stunning scenery. Explore the distinctive flora and fauna at the neighbouring Khangchendzonga National Park, immerse yourself in Buddhist spirituality at Rumtek Monastery, or just take a leisurely stroll along the MG Marg, the city\'s lively promenade, while indulging in local fare and handicrafts. In the heart of the Himalayas, Gangtok is a sanctuary for tourists looking for adventure and leisure thanks to its unique blend of modernity and culture.', '', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Gangtok (4).jpg,Gangtok (3).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d56706.18135408105!2d88.5792751332259!3d27.34020590204898!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39e6a56a5805eafb%3A0x73d6132c501c8f20!2sGangtok%2C%20Sikkim!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v171817100069'),
(125, 'Lachung', '1', 'Shiv', 'Lachung (2).jpg', '21', 'Lachung, a charming village known for its breathtaking natural beauty and peaceful atmosphere, is a secluded Himalayan getaway tucked away in the North Sikkim region of the Indian state of Sikkim. Lachung, which is 2,750 metres above sea level, provides amazing vistas of snow-capped peaks, verdant valleys, and cascading waterfalls. Known as the \"Valley of Flowers,\" visitors to this picturesque location can explore the lovely Yumthang Valley, where alpine meadows blossom in a riot of colours in the spring. Additionally, Lachung serves as a starting point for exploring North Sikkim\'s higher altitude areas, which include the breathtaking Zero Point scenery and the world\'s highest lake, Gurudongmar Lake. Lachung\'s calm ambiance and unspoiled beauty', '', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Lachung (5).jpg,Lachung (4).jpg,Lachung (3).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d7065.734874352574!2d88.73788118944778!3d27.690491754874525!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39e6cdb01406c43d%3A0xf34a0c13f69785b9!2sLachung%2C%20Sikkim%20737120!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1'),
(126, 'Yumthang', '1', 'Shiv', 'Yumthang (2).jpg', '21', 'The enchanting high-altitude sanctuary known as Yumthang Valley, or the \"Valley of Flowers,\" is tucked away in the North Sikkim region of the Indian state of Sikkim. This picturesque valley, which sits at an elevation of about 3,500 metres, enthrals tourists with its rainbow of hues in the spring when alpine meadows explode with an abundance of different kinds of wildflowers. Yumthang, surrounded by snow-capped peaks and sprinkled with pure streams, provides a tranquil haven amidst breathtakingly beautiful surroundings. The valley is a must-visit location for nature lovers and photographers alike because, in addition to its floral beauty, it offers chances for walking, picnicking, and hot spring exploration.', '', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Yumthang (4).jpg,Yumthang (3).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d56454.98330726068!2d88.65734933818091!3d27.827112342387785!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39e6d6b31b80f707%3A0x1eabb09edbb663ae!2sYumthang%2C%20Sikkim%20737120!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v'),
(127, 'Kalimpong', '1', 'Shiv', 'Kalimpong (2).jpg', '146', 'Misty mountains, lush valleys, and colonial-era buildings combine to create the quaint appeal of Kalimpong, a picturesque hill station located in the Indian state of West Bengal. Positioned at a height of roughly 1,250 metres, this serene town provides sweeping views of the majestic Himalayas and the Teesta River meandering through the valley below. With its rich foliage and mild environment, Kalimpong draws tourists looking for a break from the hustle and bustle of the metropolis. Vibrant marketplaces, elaborate monasteries, and old cathedrals showcase the town\'s rich cultural legacy, and its tea estates and flower nurseries contribute to its picturesque landscape. Trekking and river rafting in the nearby area are popular activities, or you may just spend time exploring Kalimpong\'s narrow streets filled with traditional Tibetan handicraft stores.', '', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Kalimpong (4).jpg,Kalimpong (3).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d56847.832578692556!2d88.43604563043596!3d27.06207823436844!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39e421ff94ad4ae1%3A0x1afb5b8db2de1c2f!2sKalimpong%2C%20West%20Bengal!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1'),
(128, 'Lachen', '1', 'Shiv', 'Lachen (2).jpg', '21', 'Lachen, a serene village tucked away in the remote reaches of North Sikkim, India, stands as a gateway to some of the Himalayas\' most pristine and breathtaking landscapes. Situated at an altitude of around 2,750 meters, Lachen serves as a base for exploring the rugged terrain and high-altitude wonders of the region. From here, travelers embark on journeys to stunning destinations like Gurudongmar Lake, one of the world\'s highest lakes, where shimmering waters reflect the surrounding snow-capped peaks. Lachen itself boasts a tranquil ambiance, with its traditional Tibetan architecture, prayer flags fluttering in the breeze, and warm hospitality welcoming visitors to immerse themselves in the beauty and culture of the Himalayas. Whether trekking through alpine meadows, encountering diverse flora and fauna, or simply reveling in the serenity of this mountainous paradise, Lachen offers an unforgettable experience for those seeking adventure and solace amidst nature\'s grandeur.', '', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Lachen (4).jpg,Lachen (3).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d56506.9033025535!2d88.51213828715598!3d27.72711987682157!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39e6dcac5ae61bff%3A0x9ee8cb94b7e7964a!2sLachen%2C%20Sikkim%20737120!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1718'),
(129, 'Dharamshala', '1', 'Shiv', 'Dharamshala (2).jpg', '1', 'Dharamshala is a mesmerising hill station known for its spiritual aura, breathtaking vistas, and Tibetan culture. It is located in the scenic Kangra Valley of Himachal Pradesh, India. The location is known for housing the Tibetan government-in-exile and the Dalai Lama. It is split into upper and lower districts, with McLeod Ganj acting as the bustling upper town and Dharamshala as the lower town. Wanderers can take in the breathtaking scenery of the Dhauladhar Range while exploring the peaceful monasteries, like the Namgyal Monastery and Tsuglagkhang Complex. The town\'s vibrant marketplaces provide a variety of handcrafted items from Tibet, flavorful teas, and delicious food, and its tranquil atmosphere and expansive views make it a sanctuary for nature lovers, spiritual seekers, and cultural enthusiasts alike. The special attraction of Dharamshala.', 'Residence of Dalai Lama, Tiesto Monasterio, Kangda Fort, Mcleodganj ', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Dharamshala (4).jpg,Dharamshala (3).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d27004.263703675362!2d76.29856558917038!3d32.216813188215404!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x391b50df65bd7311%3A0x3e08bdb100c6dc10!2sDharamshala%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh!5e0!3m2!1sen!'),
(131, 'Nalagarh ', '1', 'Shiv', 'Nalagarh Chail.jpg', '1', 'Nalagarh and Chail, situated in the Indian state of Himachal Pradesh, offer contrasting yet equally enchanting experiences for travelers. Nalagarh, with its historic fort perched atop a hill, exudes old-world charm and regal elegance, inviting visitors to immerse themselves in centuries of history and architectural splendor. The fort\'s sprawling grounds and panoramic views of the surrounding Shivalik Hills provide a serene retreat amidst nature\'s beauty. In contrast, Chail, nestled amidst lush green forests and majestic mountains, offers a tranquil escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. Known for its pristine natural beauty and serene ambiance, Chail beckons travelers with its scenic hiking trails, serene temples, and the world\'s highest cricket ground. Whether exploring Nalagarh\'s regal heritage or finding serenity in Chail\'s natural landscapes, these destinations promise unforgettable experiences for those seeking a blend of history, culture, and nature in the heart of the Himalayas.Nalagarh is a beautiful hill station in Solan district of Himachal Pradesh. Once an important kingdom, Nalagarh wa', 'Nalagarh Fort', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'nalagarh chail (3).jpg,nalagarh chail (2).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d27368.544512548924!2d77.17277508555503!3d30.9685827144038!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x390f7ff448852819%3A0x3580141bd7f106e6!2sChail%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20173217!5e0!3m2!1sen'),
(132, 'Kullu', '1', 'Shiv', 'kullu (2).jpg', '1', 'Kullu, in the Indian state of Himachal Pradesh, is a charming valley known for its breathtaking natural beauty, rich cultural legacy, and exciting adventure options. It is tucked away in the foothills of the Himalayas. Kullu, surrounded by snow-capped peaks, verdant forests, and the shimmering Beas River winding through its centre, enthrals tourists with its tranquil atmosphere and expansive views. Discovering historic temples and bustling marketplaces to partaking in exhilarating outdoor pursuits like trekking, river rafting, and paraglidingâ€”Kullu provides an array of experiences that make it a popular vacation spot for nature lovers, adrenaline seekers, and culture vultures alike.', 'Bijli Mahadev Temple, Raghunath Temple, Great Himalayan National Park, Solang Valley, Hadimba Temple, Vashisht Temple', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'kullu (4).jpg,kullu (3).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d27081.85066718708!2d77.0906927383992!3d31.95462029991889!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3904f6a95c673edb%3A0x40f8c144f79ad609!2sKullu%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20175101!5e0!3m2!1sen!'),
(133, 'Calangute', '1', 'Shiv', 'Calangute.jpg', '3', 'Calangute, which is tucked away in North Goa, India, is the perfect example of the typical Goan experience because of its immaculate beaches, colourful culture, and energetic vibe. Every corner of Calangute beckons with adventure and discovery, from the sun-drenched sands of Calangute Beach, where guests may unwind, swim, and engage in exhilarating water sports, to the ancient elegance of St. Alex Church, a reminder of the area\'s colonial heritage. With their wide selection of handicrafts, apparel, and unique local items, the crowded markets provide a sensory experience, and the vibrant nightlife creates the perfect backdrop for amazing evenings spent dancing outside. Travellers looking to experience the spirit of Goa\'s coastal appeal will find an engaging and enthralling experience in Calangute, with its blend of natural beauty, cultural legacy, and vibrant energy.', 'Calangute Beach,St. Alex Church,Calangute Market,Baga Beach,Fort Aguada', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Calangute (3).jpg,Calangute (2).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d61502.15687365702!2d73.72722718635373!3d15.5443049256013!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3bbfc1e37dbb59f5%3A0x9d0f9711b731c786!2sCalangute%2C%20Goa%20403519!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1718'),
(134, 'Candolim', '1', 'Shiv', 'Candolim.jpg', '3', 'Nestled in the picturesque coastal region of North Goa, India, Candolim offers a mesmerising combination of vibrant culture, rich history, and immaculate beaches. Candolim Beach welcomes guests to enjoy exhilarating water sports experiences or relax in its tranquil atmosphere, with its scenic shores lapped by the Arabian Sea\'s azure seas. With its Baroque architecture and spectacular views of the coastline, the historic Aguada Fort stands guard silently, while the Church of St. Lawrence radiates a timeless charm. With their kaleidoscope of colours and flavours, bustling markets entice visitors and offer an insight into the way of life there. With activities ranging from peaceful walks along the shore to in-depth investigations of its historical sites, Candolim offers visitors an amazing trip into the heart of Goa\'s coastal region.', 'Candolim Beach,Aguada Fort,Church of St. Lawrence,Candolim Market', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Candolim Market.jpg,Aguada Fort.jpg,Candolim (2).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d30756.155213064143!2d73.74965485306868!3d15.510262248950115!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3bbfc1a3ca96d9fb%3A0xd4400f3dbaa7b588!2sCandolim%2C%20Goa!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v17182814176'),
