(244, 'Yogyakarta City (Yogyakarta/Jogja)', '1', 'Shiv', 'Yogyakarta Special Region (2).jpg', '79', 'With a blend of history, art, and Javanese friendliness, Yogyakarta City, also referred to as Jogja, is a cultural and educational hub in Java, Indonesia. It is well-known for its kraton (royal palace), traditional puppetry, and lively street art scene.', 'Borobudur Temple, Prambanan Temple, Kraton Yogyakarta (Yogyakarta Palace), Malioboro Street, Taman Sari Water Castle', '', '1', '1', '10000', 'Yogyakarta City (YogyakartaJogja) (5).jpg,Yogyakarta City (YogyakartaJogja) (6).jpg,Yogyakarta City (YogyakartaJogja) (7).jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d63245.98371950261!2d110.33364487873297!3d-7.803163418748207!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x2e7a5787bd5b6bc5%3A0x21723fd4d3684f71!2sYogyakarta%2C%20Yogyakarta%20City%2C%20Special%20'),
