(365, 36, 42, '4', 'Agra to Delhi (230 km, 3-4 hours) / Departure', 'Visit Itimad-ud-Daulah (Baby Taj) or the Akbarâ€™s Tomb in Sikandra. Depart from Agra to Delhi. Depending on your travel schedule, explore any remaining sights or do some last-minute shopping in Delhi. Head to the airport or railway station for your onward journey.', 'Itimad-ud-Daulah,Akbarâ€™s Tomb', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01'),
(366, 37, 58, '1', 'Arrival in Ayodhya', 'Arrive in Ayodhya. Check into your hotel and freshen up. Visit the Ram Janmabhoomi, the birthplace of Lord Rama. Explore Hanuman Garhi, a temple dedicated to Lord Hanuman.', 'Ram Janmabhoomi, Hanuman Garhi, Kanak Bhawan Temple', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01'),
(367, 37, 58, '2', 'Ayodhya', 'Visit Saryu River and take a dip in its holy waters. Explore Nageshwarnath Temple, an ancient temple with significant historical importance. Visit Guptar Ghat, a serene and sacred ghat on the banks of the Saryu River. Explore Treta Ke Thakur, a temple that marks the spot where Lord Rama performed the Ashwamedha Yagna. Attend the evening Aarti on the banks of the Saryu River.', 'Saryu River,Nageshwarnath Temple,Guptar Ghat,Treta Ke Thakur', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01'),
(368, 37, 56, '3', 'Ayodhya to Varanasi (200 km, 4-5 hours)', 'Depart from Ayodhya to Varanasi. Arrive in Varanasi and check into your hotel. Visit the Kashi Vishwanath Temple, one of the most famous Hindu temples dedicated to Lord Shiva. Attend the Ganga Aarti at Dashashwamedh Ghat, a mesmerizing spiritual experience on the banks of the Ganges River.', 'Kashi Vishwanath Temple,Ganga Aarti', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01'),
(369, 37, 56, '4', 'Varanasi', 'Take an early morning boat ride on the Ganges River to witness the sunrise and the rituals performed on the ghats. Visit Sarnath, where Lord Buddha gave his first sermon after attaining enlightenment. Explore the Banaras Hindu University (BHU) and visit the Bharat Kala Bhavan Museum. Visit the Durga Temple and Tulsi Manas Temple. Stroll through the narrow lanes of Varanasi and explore the local markets for souvenirs. Head to the airport or railway station for your onward journey.', 'Ganges River,Sarnath,Banaras Hindu University,Bharat Kala Bhavan Museum,Durga Temple,Tulsi Manas Temple', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01'),
(370, 38, 58, '1', 'Arrival in Ayodhya', 'Arrive in Ayodhya. Check into your hotel and freshen up. Visit the Ram Janmabhoomi, the birthplace of Lord Rama, and explore the temple complex. Head to Hanuman Garhi, a significant temple dedicated to Lord Hanuman. Visit Kanak Bhawan Temple, known for its intricate architecture and serene environment.', ' Ram Janmabhoomi,Hanuman Garhi,Kanak Bhawan Temple', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01'),
(371, 38, 58, '2', 'Ayodhya', 'Start your day with a visit to the Saryu River and take a dip in its holy waters. Explore the Nageshwarnath Temple, an ancient temple with a rich history. Visit Guptar Ghat, a peaceful and sacred spot on the banks of the Saryu River where Lord Rama is believed to have taken Jal Samadhi. Head to Treta Ke Thakur, a temple that marks the site where Lord Rama performed the Ashwamedha Yagna. Attend the evening Aarti on the banks of the Saryu River for a spiritual experience.', 'Saryu River,Nageshwarnath Temple,Guptar Ghat,Treta Ke Thakur', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01'),
(372, 38, 58, '3', 'Ayodhya', 'Visit the Chhoti Chhawni, a temple complex with beautiful idols and gardens. Explore the Ramkatha Park, which is dedicated to the life and times of Lord Rama and has a large open-air theater for cultural performances. Visit Mani Parvat, a small hill believed to be a part of the mountain that Hanuman carried to Lanka during the Ramayana. Explore the Tulsi Smarak Bhawan, dedicated to the poet-saint Tulsidas, who wrote the Ramcharitmanas. Enjoy a peaceful walk along the Ram Ki Paidi, a series of ghats on the banks of the Saryu River.', 'Chhoti Chhawni,Ramkatha Park,Mani Parvat,Tulsi Smarak Bhawan,Ram Ki Paidi', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01'),
(373, 39, 59, '1', 'Arrival in Delhi and Travel to Mathura', 'Arrive in Delhi. Travel to Mathura (approx. 3 hours).  Arrive in Mathura and check into your hotel. Visit the Sri Krishna Janmabhoomi Temple, the birthplace of Lord Krishna. Explore the Dwarkadhish Temple, known for its beautiful architecture and spiritual significance. Visit the Vishram Ghat on the banks of the Yamuna River, where Lord Krishna is believed to have rested after defeating Kansa.', 'Sri Krishna Janmabhoomi Temple,Dwarkadhish Temple,Vishram Ghat', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01');
