(374, 39, 57, '2', 'Mathura and Vrindavan', 'Travel to Vrindavan (approx. 30 minutes). Visit the Banke Bihari Temple, one of the most famous temples in Vrindavan dedicated to Lord Krishna. Explore the ISKCON Temple, also known as Krishna Balaram Mandir. Visit the Prem Mandir, a beautiful temple complex known for its intricate marble carvings and evening light shows. Explore the Radha Raman Temple, another prominent temple in Vrindavan. Visit the Keshi Ghat on the banks of the Yamuna River and attend the evening Aarti.', 'Banke Bihari Temple,ISKCON Temple,Prem Mandir,Radha Raman Temple,Keshi Ghat', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01'),
(375, 39, 36, '3', 'Mathura to Agra (approx. 1.5 hours)', 'Depart from Mathura to Agra. Visit the Taj Mahal, one of the Seven Wonders of the World and an iconic symbol of love. Explore the Agra Fort, a massive red sandstone fort that served as the main residence of the Mughal emperors. Visit the Mehtab Bagh for a sunset view of the Taj Mahal across the Yamuna River.', 'Taj Mahal,Agra Fort,Mehtab Bagh', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-01'),
