(633, 83, 148, '6', 'Queenstown to Rotorua', 'Fly or drive to Rotorua, famous for its geothermal wonders and Maori culture. Visit the Wai-O-Tapu Thermal Wonderland to marvel at geysers and hot springs. In the evening, experience a traditional Maori hangi feast and cultural performance at a local village.', 'Wai-O-Tapu Thermal Wonderland,Maori hangi feast', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(634, 83, 0, '7', 'Rotorua Exploration & Departure', 'Spend your final day exploring Rotorua\'s attractions. Visit Te Puia to see geysers, or unwind at the Polynesian Spa. Explore the Redwoods Forest for some light hiking or biking. In the afternoon, travel back to Auckland for your departure, concluding your immersive 7-day exploration of New Zealand.', '', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(635, 84, 61, '1', 'Arrival in Auckland', 'Arrive in Auckland, New Zealandâ€™s largest city. After checking into your hotel, start your journey by exploring the cityâ€™s vibrant heart. Visit the Sky Tower for panoramic views of the city, stroll through Viaduct Harbour, and explore the bustling Queen Street. Enjoy a delicious dinner at a waterfront restaurant.', 'Sky Tower,Viaduct Harbour,Queen Street', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(636, 84, 61, '2', 'Auckland Exploration', 'Spend the day discovering Aucklandâ€™s cultural and natural highlights. Visit the Auckland War Memorial Museum to delve into New Zealandâ€™s history and culture, followed by a trip to Auckland Domain. In the afternoon, take a ferry to Waiheke Island for a wine tasting experience or relax on its stunning beaches. Return to Auckland for an evening at leisure.', 'Auckland War Memorial Museum,Auckland Domain,Waiheke Island', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(637, 84, 63, '3', 'Travel to Christchurch', 'Fly to Christchurch, the Garden City. After checking in, explore the serene Botanic Gardens and the Christchurch Art Gallery. Take a leisurely punt ride on the Avon River and stroll through the quirky Re Mall. Conclude the day with a delightful dinner in one of the city\'s top eateries.', 'Botanic Gardens,Christchurch Art Gallery,Avon River,Re Mall', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(638, 84, 63, '4', ' Christchurch Sightseeing', 'Explore Christchurchâ€™s vibrant arts and culture scene. Visit the Canterbury Museum and explore the Street Art Trail around the city. Take a scenic drive to Sumner Beach for some relaxation by the sea. Enjoy a relaxing evening with dinner at a local restaurant.', 'Canterbury Museum,Street Art Trail,Sumner Beach', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(639, 84, 64, '5', 'Christchurch to Greymouth via TranzAlpine', 'Embark on the famous TranzAlpine train journey from Christchurch to Greymouth. Enjoy breathtaking views of the Southern Alps and lush rainforests. Upon arrival in Greymouth, visit the Shantytown Heritage Park to step back in time to the gold rush era. Spend the evening at leisure exploring this charming town.', 'TranzAlpine train journey,Shantytown Heritage Park', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(640, 84, 148, '6', 'Greymouth to Rotorua', 'Travel to Rotorua, the geothermal wonderland of New Zealand. After checking into your accommodation, visit the Wai-O-Tapu Thermal Wonderland to witness its spectacular geysers and colorful hot springs. In the evening, experience a traditional Maori hangi feast and cultural performance, immersing yourself in the rich Maori culture.', 'Wai-O-Tapu Thermal Wonderland,Maori hangi feast', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(641, 84, 148, '7', 'Rotorua Adventures', 'Spend the day exploring Rotoruaâ€™s many attractions. Visit Te Puia to see the Pohutu Geyser, explore the Redwoods Forest for some light hiking or biking, and unwind at the Polynesian Spa with a relaxing soak in the natural hot springs. Enjoy dinner at a local restaurant, with options ranging from traditional Maori cuisine to international fare.', 'Te Puia,Pohutu Geyser,Redwoods Forest,Polynesian Spa', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(642, 84, 61, '8', 'Rotorua to Auckland', 'Travel back to Auckland and spend your day exploring the cityâ€™s diverse attractions. Visit the Auckland Zoo or the Sea Life Kelly Tarlton\'s Aquarium. In the afternoon, relax at Mission Bay Beach or explore the boutique shops in Ponsonby. Enjoy a farewell dinner at one of Aucklandâ€™s top restaurants.', 'Auckland Zoo,Sea Life Kelly Tarlton Aquarium,Mission Bay Beach,Ponsonby', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(643, 84, 63, '9', 'Auckland to Christchurch', 'Fly back to Christchurch to explore more of the South Island. Spend your day discovering the Banks Peninsula, with a visit to Akaroa where you can enjoy a dolphin-watching cruise or explore the charming French-inspired town. Return to Christchurch in the evening for a relaxing night.', 'Banks Peninsula,Akaroa', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(644, 84, 63, '10', 'Christchurch Day Trip', 'Take a day trip to explore the stunning landscapes surrounding Christchurch. Consider a visit to Arthurâ€™s Pass National Park for hiking and nature walks, or explore the Waipara Wine Region for wine tasting. Return to Christchurch in the evening to enjoy a leisurely dinner and reflect on your journey.', 'Arthur Pass National Park,Waipara Wine Region', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(645, 84, 0, '11', 'Departure', 'Spend your final morning enjoying the last moments in Christchurch. Take a leisurely breakfast, explore any remaining sights, or do some last-minute shopping for souvenirs. Check out of your hotel and transfer to the airport for your departure, concluding your amazing 11-day tour of New Zealand with unforgettable memories of its diverse landscapes and vibrant cities.', '', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(646, 85, 61, '1', 'Arrival in Auckland', 'Arrive in Auckland, New Zealandâ€™s bustling gateway. After checking into your hotel, start your exploration by visiting the Auckland War Memorial Museum to delve into New Zealandâ€™s rich history and Maori culture. Later, take a stroll through the Auckland Domain and enjoy a relaxed evening in the city center.', 'Auckland War Memorial Museum,Auckland Domain', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(647, 85, 61, '2', 'Auckland City Tour', 'Explore Aucklandâ€™s vibrant neighborhoods and scenic spots. Begin with a visit to the Sky Tower for panoramic city views, followed by a leisurely walk around Viaduct Harbour. In the afternoon, take a ferry to Devonport, a charming seaside village with historic buildings and stunning views of Aucklandâ€™s skyline. Return to the city for dinner at one of Aucklandâ€™s top restaurants.', 'Sky Tower,Viaduct Harbour,Devonport', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(648, 85, 148, '3', 'Auckland to Rotorua', 'Travel to Rotorua, the cultural heart of New Zealand and a geothermal wonderland. After checking in, visit the Wai-O-Tapu Thermal Wonderland to see its spectacular geysers and colorful hot springs. In the evening, immerse yourself in Maori culture with a traditional hangi feast and cultural performance at a local village.', ' Wai-O-Tapu Thermal Wonderland, hangi feast', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(649, 85, 148, '4', 'Rotorua Exploration', 'Spend the day exploring Rotoruaâ€™s unique attractions. Start with a visit to Te Puia to witness the Pohutu Geyser and explore the Maori Arts and Crafts Institute. Then, venture into the Redwoods Forest for a walk or bike ride through towering trees. Relax in the evening with a soak in the natural hot springs at the Polynesian Spa.', 'Te Puia,Pohutu Geyser,Redwoods Forest, Polynesian Spa', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(650, 85, 63, '5', 'Rotorua to Christchurch', 'Fly to Christchurch, known as the Garden City. Upon arrival, explore the serene Botanic Gardens and take a punt ride on the Avon River. In the afternoon, visit the Canterbury Museum and enjoy a walk through the Re Mall. Conclude your day with dinner in one of the city\'s charming restaurants.', 'Botanic Gardens,Avon River,Canterbury Museum,Re Mall', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(651, 85, 63, '6', 'Christchurch Exploration', 'Spend the day discovering Christchurchâ€™s blend of traditional and modern influences. Visit the Christchurch Art Gallery and explore the cityâ€™s vibrant street art. Take a scenic drive to Sumner Beach for some relaxation, or visit Akaroa for a taste of French culture in New Zealand. Enjoy a relaxed evening in the city.', 'Christchurch Art Gallery,Sumner Beach,Akaroa', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(652, 85, 65, '7', 'Christchurch to Queenstown', 'Travel to Queenstown, the adventure capital of New Zealand. After checking in, take a leisurely stroll around Lake Wakatipu and visit the Queenstown Gardens. In the evening, take the Skyline Gondola to Bobâ€™s Peak for stunning views.', 'Lake Wakatipu,Queenstown Gardens,Skyline Gondola,Bob Peak', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(653, 85, 65, '8', 'Queenstown Adventures', 'Experience the thrill of Queenstownâ€™s outdoor activities. Choose from bungee jumping, skydiving, or a jet boat ride on the Shotover River. For a more relaxed option, take a scenic cruise on Milford Sound. Spend the evening exploring Queenstownâ€™s lively nightlife or dining at a lakeside restaurant.', 'bungee jumping, skydiving, jet boat ride,Milford Sound', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(654, 85, 65, '9', 'Queenstown Exploration', 'Take a day to explore Queenstownâ€™s surroundings. Visit Arrowtown, a charming historic gold mining town, or take a trip to Glenorchy for breathtaking scenery. In the evening, return to Queenstown for a relaxing dinner and stroll along the lake.', 'Arrowtown,Glenorchy ', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(655, 85, 63, '10', 'Queenstown to Christchurch', 'Fly back to Christchurch for the final leg of your journey. Spend your day exploring more of the South Islandâ€™s beauty. Take a day trip to Arthurâ€™s Pass National Park for hiking and nature walks, or visit the Waipara Wine Region for wine tasting. Return to Christchurch in the evening.', 'Arthur Pass National Park,Waipara Wine Region', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(656, 85, 173, '11', 'Day Trip to Mount Cook', 'Take a day trip from Christchurch to Mount Cook, New Zealandâ€™s highest peak. Enjoy scenic drives through the Southern Alps and spend time exploring the stunning landscapes of Aoraki/Mount Cook National Park. Return to Christchurch in the evening, reflecting on the natural beauty of the country.', ' Mount Cook,Aoraki/Mount Cook National Park', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(657, 85, 0, '12', 'Departure', 'Spend your final morning in Christchurch with a leisurely breakfast and some last-minute sightseeing or shopping. Check out of your hotel and transfer to the airport for your departure, concluding your traditional 12-day journey through New Zealand with memories of its rich culture, stunning landscapes, and vibrant cities.', '', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(658, 86, 66, '1', 'Arrival in Kathmandu', 'Arrive in Kathmandu, the vibrant capital of Nepal. After settling in, start your exploration with a visit to the Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple), a UNESCO World Heritage site offering panoramic views of the city. Spend the evening strolling through the bustling streets of Thamel, where you can enjoy dinner at a local restaurant and experience the vibrant nightlife.', 'Swayambhunath Stupa,Thamel', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(659, 86, 66, '2', 'Kathmandu Valley Exploration', 'Begin your day with a visit to the iconic Pashupatinath Temple, one of the most sacred Hindu temples in the world. Continue to the Boudhanath Stupa, a significant pilgrimage site for Buddhists, known for its massive mandala. In the afternoon, explore Patan Durbar Square, renowned for its exquisite Newari architecture. Return to Kathmandu in the evening for a relaxing dinner.', 'Pashupatinath Temple,Boudhanath Stupa,Patan Durbar Square', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(660, 86, 174, '3', 'Day Trip to Bhaktapur', 'Take a day trip to Bhaktapur, a well-preserved medieval city just outside Kathmandu. Explore the historic Bhaktapur Durbar Square, the Nyatapola Temple, and the Pottery Square where you can witness traditional pottery making. Enjoy lunch at a local cafÃ© before returning to Kathmandu. Spend the evening at leisure, perhaps shopping for souvenirs in Thamel.', 'Bhaktapur,Bhaktapur Durbar Square,Nyatapola Temple,Pottery Square', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(661, 86, 66, '4', 'Cultural Immersion in Kathmandu', 'Immerse yourself in the local culture with a morning visit to Kopan Monastery for a peaceful experience and a glimpse into Tibetan Buddhism. Then, visit the Garden of Dreams, a tranquil oasis in the heart of the city. In the afternoon, explore Kathmandu Durbar Square and the nearby Kumari Ghar, home to the living goddess. End your day with a traditional Nepali dinner, complete with a cultural dance performance.', 'Kopan Monastery,Garden of Dreams,Kathmandu Durbar Square,Kumari Ghar', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(662, 86, 0, '5', 'Departure', 'On your final day, enjoy a leisurely breakfast and take a morning walk around the city or visit any remaining sights. Depending on your flight schedule, you may have time to visit the Asan Bazaar for last-minute shopping. Check out of your hotel and transfer to the airport for your departure, concluding your quick yet enriching 5-day trip to Kathmandu, Nepal.', '', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(663, 87, 66, '1', 'Arrival in Kathmandu', 'Arrive in Kathmandu, the cultural heart of Nepal. After checking into your hotel, start with a visit to the Pashupatinath Temple, a UNESCO World Heritage site and one of the most sacred Hindu temples. Continue to the Boudhanath Stupa, a significant Buddhist pilgrimage site. Spend the evening exploring Thamel, a bustling area known for its shops and restaurants.', 'Pashupatinath Temple,Boudhanath Stupa,Thamel', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(664, 87, 67, '2', 'Kathmandu to Pokhara and Muktinath Visit', 'Early morning, take a scenic flight to Pokhara, the gateway to the Annapurna region. Upon arrival, drive to Jomsom and then to Muktinath, a sacred site for both Hindus and Buddhists. After visiting the Muktinath Temple, known for its 108 water spouts and eternal flame, return to Pokhara. Spend the evening relaxing by Phewa Lake or exploring the lakeside area.', 'Jomsom,Muktinath, Muktinath Temple,Phewa Lake', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(665, 87, 67, '3', 'Pokhara Exploration', 'Start your day with a visit to the Sarangkot Viewpoint for a breathtaking sunrise over the Himalayas. Explore Devi\'s Fall, the mysterious Gupteshwor Cave, and the serene World Peace Pagoda. In the afternoon, enjoy a boat ride on Phewa Lake with views of the Tal Barahi Temple. Spend the evening at leisure, enjoying the peaceful ambiance of Pokhara.', 'Sarangkot Viewpoint,Devi Fall,Gupteshwor Cave,Gupteshwor Cave,Phewa Lake,Tal Barahi Temple', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(666, 87, 66, '4', 'Return to Kathmandu and Departure', 'Fly back to Kathmandu in the morning. Depending on your flight schedule, take some time to explore Kathmandu Durbar Square or visit the Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple) for panoramic views of the city. Afterward, check out of your hotel and transfer to the airport for your departure, concluding your spiritually enriching 4-day Nepal tour with a visit to Muktinath.', 'Kathmandu Durbar Square,Swayambhunath Stupa', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(667, 88, 66, '1', 'Arrival in Kathmandu', 'Arrive in Kathmandu, the vibrant capital of Nepal. After settling into your hotel, begin your journey with a visit to the Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple), where you can enjoy panoramic views of the city. Spend the evening exploring the lively streets of Thamel, known for its eclectic mix of shops, cafes, and restaurants.', 'Swayambhunath Stupa,Thamel', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(668, 88, 66, '2', 'Cultural Exploration of Kathmandu', 'Start your day with a visit to the Pashupatinath Temple, one of the most sacred Hindu temples dedicated to Lord Shiva. Continue to the Boudhanath Stupa, a UNESCO World Heritage site and one of the largest stupas in the world. In the afternoon, explore Patan Durbar Square, known for its stunning Newari architecture and rich cultural heritage. Return to Kathmandu in the evening for a traditional Nepali dinner.', 'Pashupatinath Temple, Boudhanath Stupa,Patan Durbar Square', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(669, 88, 66, '3', 'Kathmandu Valley Highlights', 'Discover more of Kathmandu\'s cultural gems with a visit to Kathmandu Durbar Square, a complex of palaces, courtyards, and temples, including the Kumari Ghar, home to the living goddess. Afterward, visit the Garden of Dreams, a peaceful oasis in the heart of the city. Spend the afternoon at Bhaktapur, a medieval city known for its well-preserved architecture, pottery, and vibrant local life. Return to Kathmandu for a relaxed evening.', 'Kathmandu Durbar Square,Kumari Ghar,Garden of Dreams,Bhaktapur', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(670, 88, 0, '4', 'Departure from Kathmandu', 'On your final day, enjoy a leisurely breakfast and take some time to explore any remaining sights or indulge in some last-minute shopping at Asan Bazaar. Depending on your flight schedule, you may wish to revisit a favorite spot or simply relax before your departure. Check out of your hotel and transfer to the airport, concluding your magical 4-day journey in Kathmandu.', '', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(671, 89, 66, '1', 'Arrival in Kathmandu', 'Arrive in Kathmandu, where youâ€™ll start your journey through Nepalâ€™s rich culture and history. After settling into your hotel, visit the Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple) for panoramic views of the city. Spend the evening exploring the bustling streets of Thamel, filled with vibrant shops and restaurants.', 'Swayambhunath Stupa,Thamel', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(672, 89, 66, '2', 'Kathmandu Valley Exploration', 'Explore the cultural heart of Kathmandu by visiting the Pashupatinath Temple, a sacred Hindu site. Continue to the Boudhanath Stupa, a significant pilgrimage site for Buddhists. In the afternoon, discover Patan Durbar Square, known for its stunning Newari architecture. Return to your hotel in Kathmandu for a relaxed evening.', 'Pashupatinath Temple,Boudhanath Stupa,Patan Durbar Square', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(673, 89, 67, '3', 'Kathmandu to Pokhara', 'Travel to Pokhara, the gateway to the Annapurna region. Upon arrival, enjoy the serene beauty of Phewa Lake and take a boat ride with views of the Tal Barahi Temple. In the evening, explore the lakeside area, with its relaxed ambiance and stunning mountain views.', 'Phewa Lake, Tal Barahi Temple', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(674, 89, 67, '4', 'Pokhara Adventure', 'Start your day with a visit to Sarangkot Viewpoint to witness a breathtaking sunrise over the Himalayas. Explore Devi\'s Fall and the mystical Gupteshwor Cave. In the afternoon, visit the World Peace Pagoda for panoramic views of the Pokhara Valley. Spend the evening at leisure.', 'Sarangkot Viewpoint,Devi Fall,Gupteshwor Cave,World Peace Pagoda', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(675, 89, 68, '5', 'Pokhara to Chitwan National Park', 'Depart for Chitwan National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage site renowned for its wildlife. After checking into your jungle lodge, embark on a nature walk or a visit to a nearby Tharu village to learn about the local culture. Enjoy a traditional dinner at your lodge.', 'Chitwan National Park', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(676, 89, 68, '6', 'Chitwan National Park Safari', 'Experience the rich biodiversity of Chitwan with a full day of safari activities. Start with an early morning jeep safari or elephant ride through the jungle, where you may spot rhinos, tigers, and various bird species. In the afternoon, enjoy a canoe ride on the Rapti River, followed by a jungle walk. End your day with a cultural performance by the Tharu community.', 'jeep safari,canoe ride,jungle walk', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(677, 89, 66, '7', 'Return to Kathmandu', 'Travel back to Kathmandu, where you can spend the afternoon at leisure. Consider revisiting a favorite site or shopping for souvenirs in Asan Bazaar. Enjoy a farewell dinner with traditional Nepali cuisine at a local restaurant.', 'Asan Bazaar', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(678, 89, 66, '8', 'Departure from Kathmandu', 'On your final day, relax with a leisurely breakfast and some last-minute sightseeing or shopping. Depending on your flight schedule, visit the Garden of Dreams or take a stroll through Kathmandu Durbar Square. Check out of your hotel and transfer to the airport, concluding your beautiful 8-day journey through Nepal.', 'Garden of Dreams,Kathmandu Durbar Square', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-23'),
(679, 90, 70, '1', 'Arrival in Paro - Transfer to Thimphu', 'Arrive at Paro International Airport and meet your guide for the transfer to Thimphu, Bhutan\'s capital. After checking in, visit the Tashichho Dzong, a stunning fortress and monastery that serves as the throne room of the King of Bhutan. In the evening, explore the vibrant Thimphu market, where you can browse local handicrafts and souvenirs before settling in for the night.', 'Tashichho Dzong,Thimphu market', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(680, 90, 70, '2', 'Thimphu Sightseeing', 'Begin your day with a visit to the National Memorial Chorten, a serene stupa dedicated to world peace, followed by a trip to the Buddha Dordenma, a massive statue that offers panoramic views of the valley. Continue your exploration at the Folk Heritage Museum and the National Textile Museum, where you\'ll gain insights into Bhutanese culture and traditions. Conclude the day with a visit to the Takin Preserve, home to Bhutanâ€™s unique national animal, the takin.', 'National Memorial Chorten, Buddha Dordenma, Folk Heritage Museum, National Textile Museum, Takin Preserve', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(681, 90, 69, '3', 'Thimphu - Paro', 'After breakfast, drive back to Paro and visit the Kyichu Lhakhang, one of Bhutan\'s oldest and most sacred temples. Then, explore the Paro Rinpung Dzong, a magnificent fortress-monastery rich in history and architectural beauty. Spend the evening wandering through Paro town, enjoying the local atmosphere.', 'Kyichu Lhakhang, Paro Rinpung Dzong', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(682, 90, 69, '4', 'Paro - Hike to Tigerâ€™s Nest', 'Start your day with a hike to the iconic Taktsang Monastery (Tigerâ€™s Nest), perched dramatically on a cliffside. After descending, enjoy lunch in Paro and visit the Ta Dzong, an ancient watchtower now serving as the National Museum of Bhutan. The evening is yours to relax and take in the charm of Paro.', 'Taktsang Monastery (Tigerâ€™s Nest), Ta Dzong', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(683, 90, 0, '5', 'Departure from Paro', 'After a final breakfast in Bhutan, transfer to Paro International Airport for your departure, taking with you the memories of this enchanting journey through Paro and Thimphu.', '', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(684, 91, 70, '1', ' Arrival in Paro - Transfer to Thimphu', 'Arrive at Paro International Airport and meet your guide for the drive to Thimphu, Bhutan\'s capital. En route, stop at the Tachogang Lhakhang iron chain bridge. Upon arrival in Thimphu, visit the Tashichho Dzong, a striking fortress and monastery that serves as the administrative and religious center of Bhutan. In the evening, explore the lively Thimphu market.', 'Tachogang Lhakhang, Tashichho Dzong, Thimphu market', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(685, 91, 70, '2', 'Thimphu Sightseeing', 'Begin with a visit to the National Memorial Chorten, a monument dedicated to world peace, followed by a trip to the Buddha Dordenma, offering panoramic views of the Thimphu Valley. Continue with visits to the Folk Heritage Museum, National Textile Museum, and Takin Preserve. In the afternoon, explore the Changangkha Lhakhang, one of Thimphu\'s oldest temples.', 'National Memorial Chorten, Buddha Dordenma,Folk Heritage Museum, National Textile Museum, Takin Preserve,Changangkha Lhakhang', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(686, 91, 75, '3', 'Thimphu - Punakha', 'After breakfast, drive to Punakha via the scenic Dochula Pass (3,100 meters), where you can see the 108 chortens and enjoy stunning views of the Himalayas. Upon arrival in Punakha, visit the Punakha Dzong, the \"Palace of Great Happiness,\" situated at the confluence of the Pho Chhu and Mo Chhu rivers. Later, take a short hike to the Chimi Lhakhang, also known as the Fertility Temple.', 'Dochula Pass, Punakha Dzong, Chimi Lhakhang', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(687, 91, 69, '4', 'Punakha Sightseeing - Paro', 'Explore the Khamsum Yulley Namgyal Chorten, a stunning stupa overlooking the Punakha Valley. Afterward, drive back to Paro, stopping at Simtokha Dzong, one of Bhutan\'s oldest fortresses. Upon arrival in Paro, visit the Kyichu Lhakhang, one of Bhutanâ€™s most revered temples.', 'Khamsum Yulley Namgyal Chorten, Simtokha Dzong, Kyichu Lhakhang', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(688, 91, 69, '5', 'Paro - Hike to Tigerâ€™s Nest', 'Embark on a hike to the iconic Taktsang Monastery (Tigerâ€™s Nest), perched dramatically on a cliffside. After descending, visit the Ta Dzong, now the National Museum of Bhutan, and then explore the Paro Rinpung Dzong. Spend your evening strolling through Paro town.', 'Taktsang Monastery (Tigerâ€™s Nest), Ta Dzong, Paro Rinpung Dzong', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(689, 91, 0, '6', 'Departure from Paro', 'After breakfast, transfer to Paro International Airport for your departure, carrying with you the memories of this appealing journey through Paro, Thimphu, and Punakha.', '', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(690, 92, 70, '1', 'Arrival in Paro - Transfer to Thimphu', 'Arrive at Paro International Airport and meet your guide for the drive to Thimphu. On the way, visit the Tachogang Lhakhang iron chain bridge. After checking in at your hotel in Thimphu, visit the Tashichho Dzong, a striking fortress and monastery. Spend the evening exploring the Thimphu market.', 'Tachogang Lhakhang, Tashichho Dzong, Thimphu market', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(691, 92, 70, '2', 'Thimphu Sightseeing', 'Start your day at the National Memorial Chorten, a stupa dedicated to world peace. Next, visit the Buddha Dordenma, a massive statue with spectacular valley views, and then head to the Folk Heritage Museum and National Textile Museum to immerse yourself in Bhutanese culture. Visit the Takin Preserve to see Bhutanâ€™s national animal and end your day at the Changangkha Lhakhang, one of Thimphu\'s oldest temples.', 'National Memorial Chorten, Buddha Dordenma, Folk Heritage Museum, National Textile Museum, Takin Preserve,  Changangkha Lhakhang', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(692, 92, 75, '3', ' Thimphu - Punakha', 'Drive to Punakha, passing through the scenic Dochula Pass, where you can see the 108 memorial chortens and, on a clear day, breathtaking views of the Himalayan range. Upon arrival, visit the Punakha Dzong, the majestic fortress at the confluence of the Pho Chhu and Mo Chhu rivers. Later, take a short hike to the Chimi Lhakhang, known as the Fertility Temple.', 'Dochula Pass, Punakha Dzong, Chimi Lhakhang', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(693, 92, 75, '4', 'Punakha Exploration', 'Begin with a visit to the Khamsum Yulley Namgyal Chorten, a picturesque stupa with commanding views over the Punakha Valley. Afterward, explore the Sangchhen Dorji Lhuendrup Nunnery, which offers a peaceful retreat and panoramic views of the surrounding landscape. Spend the evening enjoying the serene ambiance of Punakha.', 'Khamsum Yulley Namgyal Chorten, Sangchhen Dorji Lhuendrup Nunnery', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(694, 92, 69, '5', 'Punakha - Paro', 'After breakfast, drive back to Paro, stopping at Simtokha Dzong, the oldest fortress in Bhutan. Upon arrival in Paro, visit the Kyichu Lhakhang, one of the most sacred temples in the country. In the evening, take a leisurely walk around Paro town.', 'Simtokha Dzong, Kyichu Lhakhang', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(695, 92, 69, '6', 'Paro - Hike to Tigerâ€™s Nest', 'Set out on a hike to the iconic Taktsang Monastery (Tigerâ€™s Nest), perched on a cliffside. After returning to Paro, visit the Ta Dzong, now the National Museum of Bhutan, followed by a tour of the Paro Rinpung Dzong. Spend your evening exploring the local shops and cafes in Paro.', 'Taktsang Monastery (Tigerâ€™s Nest), Ta Dzong, Paro Rinpung Dzong', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(696, 92, 0, '7', 'Departure from Paro', 'After a final breakfast, transfer to Paro International Airport for your departure, leaving Bhutan with lasting memories of this interesting journey through Paro, Thimphu, and Punakha.', '', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(697, 93, 70, '1', 'Arrival in Paro - Transfer to Thimphu', 'Arrive at Paro International Airport, where youâ€™ll meet your guide and transfer to Thimphu. Along the way, stop at the Tachogang Lhakhang iron chain bridge. Upon reaching Thimphu, visit the Tashichho Dzong, a majestic fortress and monastery that serves as the administrative and religious center of Bhutan. In the evening, explore the vibrant Thimphu market.', 'Tachogang Lhakhang, Tashichho Dzong, Thimphu market', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(698, 93, 70, '2', 'Thimphu Sightseeing', 'Start your exploration with a visit to the National Memorial Chorten, a peaceful monument dedicated to world peace. Continue to the Buddha Dordenma, an enormous statue offering panoramic views of the Thimphu Valley. Visit the Folk Heritage Museum and National Textile Museum to delve into Bhutanese culture. End the day with a visit to the Takin Preserve, home to Bhutanâ€™s unique national animal.', 'National Memorial Chorten, Buddha Dordenma,  Folk Heritage Museum, National Textile Museum, Takin Preserve', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(699, 93, 70, '3', ' Thimphu Exploration', 'Begin your day at the Changangkha Lhakhang, a historic temple overlooking the Thimphu Valley. Next, visit the Royal Textile Academy to learn about Bhutanâ€™s rich textile tradition. Explore the Institute for Zorig Chusum, where students learn traditional Bhutanese arts and crafts. In the afternoon, visit the Simtokha Dzong, the oldest fortress in Bhutan.', 'Changangkha Lhakhang, Royal Textile Academy, Institute for Zorig Chusum, Simtokha Dzong', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(700, 93, 69, '4', 'Thimphu - Paro', 'After breakfast, drive back to Paro. Visit the Kyichu Lhakhang, one of the oldest and most sacred temples in Bhutan. Continue to the Paro Rinpung Dzong, a fortress-monastery with stunning architecture and historical significance. Spend the evening strolling around Paro town, enjoying the local shops and cafes.', 'Kyichu Lhakhang, Paro Rinpung Dzong', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(701, 93, 69, '5', ' Paro - Hike to Tigerâ€™s Nest', 'Embark on a hike to the iconic Taktsang Monastery (Tigerâ€™s Nest), dramatically perched on a cliffside. After descending, visit the Ta Dzong, an ancient watchtower that now houses the National Museum of Bhutan. Enjoy some leisure time in Paro in the evening.', 'Taktsang Monastery (Tigerâ€™s Nest),  Ta Dzong', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
(702, 93, 0, '6', 'Departure from Paro', 'After a final breakfast in Bhutan, transfer to Paro International Airport for your departure, taking with you the memories of this fascinating journey through Paro and Thimphu.', '', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-27'),
