(1067, 139, 100, '1', 'Arrival in MahÃ© & Beau Vallon Beach', 'Welcome to the breathtaking Seychelles! After landing in MahÃ©, the largest island, transfer to your hotel and take some time to unwind. In the afternoon, head to Beau Vallon Beach, famous for its powdery white sand and turquoise waters. Enjoy swimming, sunbathing, or trying out water sports like snorkeling and jet-skiing. As the day ends, relish a delicious Creole dinner at a beachfront restaurant while watching the stunning sunset over the Indian Ocean.', 'Beau Vallon Beach', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1068, 139, 282, '2', 'Explore Victoria & Morne Seychellois National Park', 'Begin your day with a visit to Victoria, the charming capital of Seychelles. Explore the lively Sir Selwyn Clarke Market, where you can find fresh fruits, spices, and local crafts. Donâ€™t miss the Victoria Clock Tower, a replica of Londonâ€™s Big Ben, and the serene Botanical Gardens, home to giant tortoises and exotic plants. In the afternoon, embark on a hike through the Morne Seychellois National Park, where trails lead you through lush forests to panoramic viewpoints with breathtaking views of the island and the ocean.', 'Sir Selwyn Clarke Market, Victoria Clock Tower, Botanical Gardens, Morne Seychellois National Park', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1069, 139, 101, '3', 'Transfer to Praslin Island & VallÃ©e de Mai Nature Reserve', 'After breakfast, take a ferry or a short flight to Praslin Island, the second-largest island in Seychelles. Upon arrival, check into your hotel and get ready to explore the UNESCO-listed VallÃ©e de Mai Nature Reserve. Wander through the ancient palm forest, home to the rare coco de mer palms and the elusive black parrot. In the afternoon, visit Anse Lazio, one of the most beautiful beaches in the world, known for its soft white sand and crystal-clear waters. Spend your time swimming, snorkeling, or simply relaxing on the beach.', 'Praslin Island, VallÃ©e de Mai Nature Reserve, Anse Lazio', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1070, 139, 196, '4', 'Island Hopping to La Digue', 'Embark on a day trip to the nearby La Digue Island, famous for its laid-back atmosphere and stunning beaches. Rent a bicycle to explore the island at your own pace. Visit Anse Source d\'Argent, renowned for its pink granite boulders and clear, shallow waters, making it one of the most photographed beaches in the world. Explore the islandâ€™s lush interior, visit the historic Lâ€™Union Estate, and enjoy a leisurely lunch at a local restaurant. Return to Praslin in the evening.', ' La Digue Island, Anse Source d\'Argent, Lâ€™Union Estate', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
