(1101, 143, 131, '1', 'Melbourneâ€™s Highlights', 'Start your day at Federation Square, exploring its unique architecture and visiting the Ian Potter Centre and ACMI (Australian Centre for the Moving Image). A short walk will lead you to Flinders Street Station, an iconic Melbourne landmark. Afterward, head to the Royal Botanic Gardens for a relaxing stroll through its beautifully landscaped gardens and tranquil lakes. If you\'re a sports enthusiast, visit the Melbourne Cricket Ground (MCG) for a tour and explore the sports museum. In the evening, wander along Southbank for a lively atmosphere and dining options with riverside views, and consider a visit to the Eureka Skydeck for panoramic views of the city.', 'Federation Square, Ian Potter Centre, ACMI (Australian Centre for the Moving Image),  Flinders Street Station, Royal Botanic Gardens, Melbourne Cricket Ground (MCG), Southbank , Eureka Skydeck', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1102, 143, 131, '2', 'Culture and Laneways', 'Begin at the bustling Queen Victoria Market, where you can explore fresh produce, gourmet foods, and unique souvenirs. Next, visit the Melbourne Museum and Royal Exhibition Building to discover Australiaâ€™s natural and cultural history. Spend your afternoon exploring Melbourneâ€™s famous laneways such as Hosier Lane for vibrant street art, and Degraves Street and Centre Place for quirky cafes and boutique shops. Donâ€™t miss the National Gallery of Victoria for its impressive art collection. In the evening, head to Melbourneâ€™s Chinatown for a diverse range of Asian cuisines, or explore Lygon Street for Italian dining and gelato.', 'Queen Victoria Market, Melbourne Museum, Royal Exhibition Building, Hosier Lane, Degraves Street, Centre Place, National Gallery of Victoria, Melbourneâ€™s Chinatown, Lygon Street', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1103, 143, 0, '3', 'Day Trip Options', 'Choose from a day trip to Phillip Island, where you can witness the Penguin Parade at sunset, visit the Koala Conservation Centre, and enjoy coastal views at the Nobbies Centre. Alternatively, explore part of the Great Ocean Road, visiting stunning landmarks like the Twelve Apostles and Loch Ard Gorge, or enjoy a wine tour in the Yarra Valley, sampling wines and savoring a gourmet lunch. Return to Melbourne in the evening to relax and perhaps revisit Federation Square or enjoy a casual dinner at one of the city\'s vibrant dining spots.', '', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1104, 144, 102, '1', ' Iconic Sydney Sights', 'Begin your Sydney adventure at Circular Quay, where you can marvel at the Sydney Opera House and the Sydney Harbour Bridge. Take a walk through the Royal Botanic Garden for stunning views of the harbor and a tranquil escape. Visit The Rocks to explore its historic streets and vibrant markets. In the afternoon, head to Bondi Beach to relax on its famous sands or take a dip in the ocean. Finish your day with a dinner cruise on Sydney Harbour, enjoying the illuminated cityscape.', 'Circular Quay, Sydney Opera House, Sydney Harbour Bridge, Royal Botanic Garden, The Rocks, Bondi Beach', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1105, 144, 102, '2', 'Cultural and Scenic Highlights', 'Start with a visit to the Art Gallery of New South Wales, featuring Australian and international art collections. Afterward, explore Darling Harbour, where you can visit Taronga Zoo or the Australian National Maritime Museum. In the afternoon, take a ferry to Manly Beach for a leisurely walk along the promenade and some relaxation by the sea. Return to the city in the evening and enjoy a meal at one of Darling Harbourâ€™s waterfront restaurants.', 'Art Gallery of New South Wales, Darling Harbour, Taronga Zoo or the Australian National Maritime Museum, Manly Beach', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1106, 144, 102, '3', 'Day Trip to the Blue Mountains', 'Embark on a full-day excursion to the Blue Mountains. Visit Echo Point to view the Three Sisters rock formation and enjoy a walk through the lush Jamison Valley. Experience the Scenic Skyway or Scenic Railway for breathtaking views. Explore the charming town of Leura and have lunch in a local cafÃ©. Return to Sydney in the evening for a relaxed dinner, perhaps in the vibrant area of Surry Hills or Newtown.', 'Blue Mountains,  Echo Point , Three Sisters, Jamison Valley, Scenic Skyway or Scenic Railway, Leura , Surry Hills or Newtown', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1107, 144, 102, '4', 'Sydney\'s Attractions and Leisure', 'Spend the morning at Sydney Tower Eye for panoramic views of the city. Visit the Sydney Aquarium or Wild Life Sydney Zoo if you\'re interested in marine and wildlife. Explore Paddyâ€™s Market for souvenirs and a taste of local culture. In the afternoon, head to Sydney Olympic Park or take a leisurely stroll through Chinatown. Enjoy a farewell dinner at a top Sydney restaurant, reflecting on your memorable Sydney experience.', 'Sydney Tower Eye, Sydney Aquarium or Wild Life Sydney Zoo, Paddyâ€™s Market, Sydney Olympic Park , Chinatown', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
