(1124, 147, 134, '1', 'Historical Wonders of Istanbul', 'Begin your journey in the heart of Istanbul\'s historic district, Sultanahmet. Visit the magnificent Hagia Sophia, an architectural marvel that has served as both a church and a mosque. Continue to the Blue Mosque, known for its stunning blue Iznik tiles and six towering minarets. Wander through the Hippodrome, once the center of Byzantine public life, and see the Obelisk of Theodosius and the German Fountain. In the afternoon, explore the sprawling Topkapi Palace, the opulent residence of Ottoman sultans, including the Harem section. End your day with a visit to the Basilica Cistern, a fascinating underground water reservoir supported by hundreds of marble columns.', 'Sultanahmet, Hagia Sophia, Blue Mosque, Hippodrome, Obelisk of Theodosius, German Fountain,  Topkapi Palace, Harem, Basilica Cistern', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1125, 147, 202, '2', 'Vibrant Markets and Bosphorus Views', 'Start your day at the bustling Grand Bazaar, one of the largest and oldest covered markets in the world, where you can shop for everything from jewelry to spices. Afterward, head to the Spice Bazaar for a sensory overload of aromatic spices, dried fruits, and Turkish delights. In the afternoon, enjoy a leisurely Bosphorus Cruise, where you can admire Istanbul\'s skyline, palaces, and wooden Ottoman houses from the water. Disembark at the Ortakoy district, famous for its lively arts scene and charming cafes, and enjoy a traditional Turkish tea or coffee by the water.', 'Grand Bazaar, Spice Bazaar, Bosphorus Cruise, Ortakoy', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
(1126, 147, 134, '3', 'Cultural Gems and Modern Istanbul', 'Begin your day with a visit to the Dolmabahce Palace, an opulent blend of European and Ottoman architecture, and the last residence of the Ottoman sultans. Afterward, explore the vibrant neighborhood of Beyoglu, starting with Istiklal Street, a bustling pedestrian avenue lined with shops, cafes, and historic buildings. Take the nostalgic Istiklal tram to Taksim Square, the heart of modern Istanbul. In the afternoon, visit the Galata Tower for panoramic views of the city and then stroll through the artistic Galata district. End your day with a visit to the Pera Museum, which hosts a rich collection of Orientalist art.', 'Dolmabahce Palace, Beyoglu, Istiklal Street,  Istiklal tram, Taksim Square, Galata Tower, Galata, Pera Museum', '1', 'Shiv', '2024-08-29'),
