(42, 3, 'Central Region', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-07-02', 'The Central Region of Singapore include the vibrant downtown area and prominent neighbourhoods that characterise the country\'s social, cultural, and economic vitality. It is the beating heart of the island nation. The financial hub is the Downtown Core, which is home to skyscrapers like Suntec City and Marina Bay Financial Centre in addition to modern art galleries and historical buildings like the Raffles Hotel. Clarke Quay and Boat Quay offer historical charm together with busy nightlife and eating along the Singapore River, while Orchard Road beckons as a premier shopping destination with its choice of luxury stores and worldwide brands. While Bugis and Kampong Glam combine modern and traditional elements with vibrant markets, old mosques, and traditional businesses, Chinatown and Little India offer diverse cultural experiences.', 'Central Region.jpg', '', 'Central Region Tour Packages', ''),
(43, 3, 'East Region', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-07-02', 'With the smallest land area of the five, the region is the second most densely populated. The most populated town in the region is Bedok, and Tampines serves as its regional hub.', 'East Region.jpg', '', 'East Region Tour Packages', ''),
