(176, 10, 'South Island', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'The South Island of Mauritius is renowned for its rugged natural beauty, offering a more tranquil and unspoiled experience compared to the north. It features dramatic landscapes, including the iconic Le Morne Brabant, a UNESCO World Heritage site, and the stunning Chamarel Seven Colored Earths. The region is home to pristine beaches like Blue Bay, famous for its crystal-clear waters and vibrant coral reefs, ideal for snorkeling. Visitors can explore the lush Black River Gorges National Park, rich in biodiversity, or experience the islandâ€™s cultural heritage at the sacred Grand Bassin, a revered Hindu pilgrimage site. The South Island offers a perfect escape into nature and tranquility.', 'xavier-coiffic-ByAHlRiTQjo-unsplash.jpg', '', 'South Island Tour Packages', ''),
(177, 10, 'Casela Nature Park', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'Huge outdoor amusement park with safari tours, camel rides & zip-lining, plus restaurants & shops.', 'casela-nature-park-mauritius_160521-387.jpg', '', 'Casela Nature Park Tour Packages', ''),
(178, 11, 'Delphi', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'The modern town of Delphi is situated immediately west of the archaeological site of the same name. The town was created as a home for the population of Castro, which was relocated to allow for the excavation of the site of ancient Delphi.', 'julia-novodvorskaia-YD5CRxhGl1o-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Delphi Tour Packages', ''),
(179, 11, 'Delos', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'Delos is a Greek island and archaeological site in the Aegean Sea\'s Cyclades archipelago, near Mykonos. The mythological birthplace of Apollo, it was a major religious center and port during the 1st millennium B.C. The island\'s ruins encompass Doric temples, markets, an amphitheater, houses with mosaics and the iconic Terrace of the Lions statues. The Archaeological Museum displays statues excavated from the site.', 'fabrizzio-moncada-f4OQrL7JevQ-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Delos Tour Packages', ''),
(180, 12, 'Sidemen', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'Sidemen is the name for the main village as well as the surrounding area, including Selat. The locality is nestled between the valleys of central east Bali, with the majestic Mount Agung always present in the distance.', 'tom-donders-l3vSIAj58RE-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Sidemen Tour Packages', ''),
(181, 12, 'Sanur', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'Sanur is a seaside town in the southeast of the island of Bali, in Indonesia. Its long stretch of beach offers shallow waters. Colorful jukung fishing boats rest on the sand, backed by a paved cycling path. The Pura Blanjong temple is built from coral and has inscriptions dating from the 10th century. The leafy main street Jalan Danau Tamblingan is lined with art galleries and restaurants.', 'rustam-effendy-zsfK44F_PM4-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Sanur Tour Packages', ''),
(182, 12, 'Tanah Lot', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'Tanah Lot is a spectacular sea temple located on the southwest coast of Bali, Indonesia. Perched atop a dramatic rocky outcrop, it is one of Bali\'s most iconic and photographed landmarks. The temple is renowned for its breathtaking sunset views, where the setting sun creates a magical backdrop against the temple\'s silhouette. Tanah Lot is dedicated to the sea gods and is an important cultural and spiritual site for the Balinese people. During low tide, visitors can walk up to the temple, while high tide makes it appear to float on the ocean. The surrounding area features lush landscapes and traditional Balinese architecture, making Tanah Lot a must-visit destination for its natural beauty and cultural significance.', 'eyestetix-studio-CRqFC5HohC8-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Tanah Lot Tour Packages', ''),
(183, 12, 'Uluwatu', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'Uluwatu is a village on the south-western tip of the Bukit Peninsula of Bali, Indonesia. It is home to the Uluwatu temple.', 'utku-ozen-theutkuozen-nT19-hgWcFk-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Uluwatu Tour Packages', ''),
(184, 14, 'Cordoba', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'CÃ³rdoba is a city in the southern Spanish region of Andalusia, and the capital of the province of CÃ³rdoba. It was an important Roman city and a major Islamic center in the Middle Ages. Itâ€™s best known for La Mezquita, an immense mosque dating from 784 A.D., featuring a columned prayer hall and older Byzantine mosaics.', 'sergio-guardiola-herrador-29gMhnG_PEM-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Cordoba Tour Packages', ''),
(185, 13, 'Douro valley', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'The Douro is the largest river of the Iberian Peninsula by discharge. It rises near Duruelo de la Sierra in the Spanish province of Soria, meanders briefly south, then flows generally west through the northern part of the Meseta Central in Castile and LeÃ³n into northern Portugal.', 'zeynep-sumer-wO-igSizHqY-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Douro valley Tour Packages', ''),
(186, 14, 'GaudÃ­â€™s Masterpieces', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'Gaudi\'s magnum opus, the Sagrada Familia, commenced construction in 1882 and remains incomplete to this day. This iconic cathedral blends elements of Gothic styles from the past with the contemporary touch of Catalan Modernisme, resulting in a neo-Gothic aesthetic.', 'jakub-kroul-Q9_nXqvGxDg-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Gaud\'s Masterpieces Tour Packages', ''),
(187, 14, 'Montserrat', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'Montserrat is a multi-peaked mountain range near Barcelona, in Catalonia, Spain. It is part of the Catalan Pre-Coastal Range. The main peaks are Sant Jeroni, MontgrÃ³s and Les Agulles. It is well known as the site of the Benedictine abbey, Santa Maria de Montserrat, which hosts the Virgin of Montserrat sanctuary.', 'highzone-KCad8u6pxN4-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Montserrat Tour Packages', ''),
(188, 14, 'Toledo', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-27', 'Toledo is an ancient city set on a hill above the plains of Castilla-La Mancha in central Spain. The capital of the region, itâ€™s known for the medieval Arab, Jewish and Christian monuments in its walled old city. It was also the former home of Mannerist painter El Greco. The Moorish Bisagra Gate and the Sol Gate, in MudÃ©jar style, open into the old quarter, where the Plaza de Zocodover is a lively meeting place.', 'ian-deneumostier-tqbNljkGHJA-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Toledo Tour Packages', ''),
(189, 16, 'Keukenhof', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-28', 'About\r\nKeukenhof, also known as the Garden of Europe, is one of the world\'s largest flower gardens, situated in the municipality of Lisse, in the Netherlands. According to the official website, Keukenhof Park covers an area of 32 hectares and approximately 7 million flower bulbs are planted in the gardens annually.', 'maksim-shutov-_33GvE8SWG4-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Keukenhof Tour Packages', ''),
(190, 5, 'Lucerne', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-28', 'Lucerne, a compact city in Switzerland known for its preserved medieval architecture, sits amid snowcapped mountains on Lake Lucerne. Its colorful Altstadt (Old Town) is bordered on the north by 870m Museggmauer (Musegg Wall), a 14-century rampart. The covered KapellbrÃ¼cke (Chapel Bridge), built in 1333, links the Aldstadt to the Reuss River\'s right bank.', 'lin-mei-xpw5IOgLjuw-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Lucerne Tour Packages', ''),
(191, 17, 'Stonehenge', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-28', 'Stonehenge is a prehistoric megalithic structure on Salisbury Plain in Wiltshire, England, two miles west of Amesbury.', 'uliana-sova-vJGj76vFX9A-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Stonehenge Tour Packages', ''),
(192, 15, 'Murano', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-28', 'The island of Murano is renowned for its long tradition of glass-making. Ferry-loads of visitors come to explore the Museo del Vetro, which tells the story of glass through the centuries, and to shop for locally crafted souvenirs. Built in the Romanesque style, the Church of Santa Maria and San Donato has a colorful mosaic floor and supposedly houses the bones of a slain dragon.', 'balint-miko-5Zourz1foEw-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Murano Tour Packages', ''),
(193, 17, 'Montmartre', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-28', 'Montmartre is a large hill in Paris\'s northern 18th arrondissement. It is 130 m high and gives its name to the surrounding district, part of the Right Bank. Montmartre is primarily known for its artistic history, for the white-domed Basilica of the SacrÃ©-CÅ“ur on its summit, and as a nightclub district.', 'manon-leduc-IQDZT06txeU-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Montmartre Tour Packages', ''),
(194, 18, 'ÄŒeskÃ½ Krumlov', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-29', 'ÄŒeskÃ½ Krumlov is a city in the South Bohemia region of the Czech Republic. Itâ€™s bisected by the Vltava River, and dominated by its 13th-century castle. The castle has Gothic, Renaissance and baroque elements, an 11-hectare garden and an original 17th-century baroque theater. There are panoramic views of the old town and the river from the top of its round belltower.', 'anna-gru-Iypm3kDe5fs-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Krumlov Tour Packages', ''),
(195, 20, 'Versailles', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-29', 'Versailles is a commune in the department of the Yvelines, ÃŽle-de-France, renowned worldwide for the ChÃ¢teau de Versailles and the gardens of Versailles, designated UNESCO World Heritage Sites. ', 'julio-wolf-_eilSGpKYlY-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Versailles Tour Packages', ''),
(196, 21, 'La Digue', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-29', 'La Digue is an island in the Seychelles, in the Indian Ocean off East Africa. Itâ€™s known for its beaches, like Anse Source dâ€™Argent, dotted with granite boulders, on the west coast. To the south, isolated Anse Bonnet CarrÃ© Beach, with calm, shallow water, is accessible only on foot, as is Anse Cocos Beach, in a protected bay on the east coast. La Digueâ€™s diverse wildlife can be seen in the Veuve Nature Reserve.', 'datingscout-EcpuASCrFFo-unsplash.jpg', '', 'La Digue Tour Packages', ''),
(197, 22, 'Blue Mountains', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-29', 'The Blue Mountains is a rugged region west of Sydney in Australiaâ€™s New South Wales. Known for dramatic scenery, it encompasses steep cliffs, eucalyptus forests, waterfalls and villages dotted with guesthouses, galleries and gardens. Katoomba, a major town in the area, borders Blue Mountains National Park and its bushwalking trails. Echo Point affords views of the storied Three Sisters sandstone rock formation.', 'albert-s-SfmW2t8sVj4-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Blue Mountains Tour Packages', ''),
(198, 22, 'Great Ocean Road', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-29', 'The Great Ocean Road is an Australian National Heritage-listed 240-kilometre stretch of road along the south-eastern coast of Australia, between the Victorian towns of Torquay and Allansford.', 'sean-oulashin-KMn4VEeEPR8-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Great Ocean Road Tour Packages', ''),
(199, 22, 'Great Barrier Reef', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-29', 'The Great Barrier Reef is the world\'s largest coral reef system, composed of over 2,900 individual reefs and 900 islands stretching for over 2,300 kilometres over an area of approximately 344,400 square kilometres.', 'manny-moreno-X9TEqJWmM6Q-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Great Barrier Reef Tour Packages', ''),
(200, 23, 'Pamukkale', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-29', 'Pamukkale is a town in western Turkey known for the mineral-rich thermal waters flowing down white travertine terraces on a nearby hillside. It neighbors Hierapolis, an ancient Roman spa city founded around 190 B.C. Ruins there include a well-preserved theater and a necropolis with sarcophagi that stretch for 2km. The Antique Pool is famous for its submerged Roman columns, the result of an earthquake.', 'furkan-elveren-UWAKaXr-0FE-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Pamukkale Tour Packages', ''),
(201, 23, 'Ephesus', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-29', 'Ephesus is an ancient city in Turkeyâ€™s Central Aegean region, near modern-day SelÃ§uk. Its excavated remains reflect centuries of history, from classical Greece to the Roman Empire â€“ when it was the Mediterraneanâ€™s main commercial center â€“ to the spread of Christianity. Paved streets wind past squares, baths and monumental ruins. The Temple of Hadrian was built before 138 A.D. for Emperor Hadrianâ€™s visit.', 'jennifer-martin-x0bwQCSW8m0-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Ephesus Tour Packages', ''),
(202, 23, 'Bosphorus', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-29', 'The Bosporus or Bosphorus Strait is a natural strait and an internationally significant waterway located in Istanbul, Turkey. The Bosporus connects the Black Sea to the Sea of Marmara and forms one of the continental boundaries between Asia and Europe. It also divides Turkey by separating Asia minor from Thrace.', 'ahmad-bader-NkvnFyNnbYE-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Bosphorus Tour Packages', ''),
(203, 28, 'Coral Island', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-30', 'A coral island is a type of island formed from coral detritus and associated organic material.[1] It occurs in tropical and sub-tropical areas, typically as part of a coral reef which has grown to cover a far larger area under the sea. The term low island can be used to distinguish such islands from high islands, which are formed through volcanic action.[2] Low islands are formed as a result of sedimentation upon a coral reef or of the uplifting of such islands.', 'michael-DXQB5D1njMY-unsplash (1).jpg', '', 'Coral Island Tour Packages', ''),
(204, 31, 'Pahang', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-30', 'Pahang is a large state in Peninsular Malaysia. It\'s known for its mountains, rainforests and beaches, including the white sands and coral reefs of Tioman Island off the east coast. The state capital, Kuantan, is a major seaport. In the west, the gentle hills of the Cameron Highlands include resorts, tea plantations and terraced farms, and the village of Fraserâ€™s Hill resembles an English hamlet.', 'hongbin-C6G94bnJ5go-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Pahang Tour Packages', ''),
(205, 31, 'Genting Highlands', 0, 0, 0, '1', '', '2024-08-30', 'Breathe deep in Genting Highlands where, unlike nearby Kuala Lumpur, the air is fresh and clean. Aside from its resort life, visitors flock to hill station to enjoy cooler temperatures, mountain scenery, strawberry farms, and a relatively undisturbed, natural rain forest.', 'levitaran-sager-7pqVtEevGOc-unsplash.jpg', '', 'Genting Highlands Tour Packages', '');
